% Instructions
- Use @modelcontextprotocol/sdk package
- All console.log/console.error must go to stderr
- Use console.error for logging, never console.log
- Set up tool list handler to return tool schemas
- Set up tool call handler to route to appropriate tool
- Handle JSON-RPC errors according to spec
- Add startup banner to stderr with server info

% Deliverable
A TypeScript module at src/index.ts that serves as the main entry point for the MCP server.

% Implementation Assumptions
- MCP SDK provides Server and StdioServerTransport classes
- Server uses stdio for communication (stdin/stdout)
- All non-MCP output goes to stderr
- Process exits cleanly on shutdown signals
